abstract: The president seeks to reassure the public while blaming the media and Democrats for trying to score points by exaggerating the threat of the outbreak.
snippet: The president seeks to reassure the public while blaming the media and Democrats for trying to score points by exaggerating the threat of the outbreak.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump complained on Friday that Democrats and the news media were trying to scare Americans about the coronavirus to score political points against him but asserted that the outbreak had been relatively limited because of his action to stem infections.

headline_main: Trump Criticizes Media for Coverage of Coronavirus

abstract: Federal Reserve officials are watching markets as coronavirus risks spook investors, and say they will ‘act as appropriate.’
snippet: Federal Reserve officials are watching markets as coronavirus risks spook investors, and say they will ‘act as appropriate.’
lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve chair, Jerome H. Powell, in an attempt to soothe jittery investors, issued a short statement Friday afternoon reaffirming that the central bank would use its tools and “act as appropriate to support the economy.”

abstract: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will tell U.S. President Donald Trump in a phone call Friday that verbal support related to Syria's Idlib region is not enough, and that Ankara expects "actual" support, a Turkish official said.
snippet: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will tell U.S. President Donald Trump in a phone call Friday that verbal support related to Syria's Idlib region is not enough, and that Ankara expects "actual" support, a Turkish official said.
lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL — Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will tell U.S. President Donald Trump in a phone call Friday that verbal support related to Syria's Idlib region is not enough, and that Ankara expects "actual" support, a Turkish official said.
headline_main: Erdogan to Tell Trump That Turkey Expects 'Actual' Support in Syria: Official
headline_print_headline: Erdogan to Tell Trump That Turkey Expects 'Actual' Support in Syria: Official

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday pledged to de-escalate U.S.-China trade tensions, make it easier for farmers to hire foreign laborers and increase federal agricultural research.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday pledged to de-escalate U.S.-China trade tensions, make it easier for farmers to hire foreign laborers and increase federal agricultural research.
lead_paragraph: MEMPHIS — Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday pledged to de-escalate U.S.-China trade tensions, make it easier for farmers to hire foreign laborers and increase federal agricultural research.
headline_main: Bloomberg Says He Would De-escalate Trade Tensions With China
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Says He Would De-escalate Trade Tensions With China

abstract: Several thousand Muslims marched from the main mosque in Bangladesh's capital on Friday to denounce India's government for allegedly inflaming tensions between Hindus and Muslims, leading to clashes that left at least 40 dead and hundreds injured.
snippet: Several thousand Muslims marched from the main mosque in Bangladesh's capital on Friday to denounce India's government for allegedly inflaming tensions between Hindus and Muslims, leading to clashes that left at least 40 dead and hundreds injured.
lead_paragraph: DHAKA, Bangladesh — Several thousand Muslims marched from the main mosque in Bangladesh's capital on Friday to denounce India's government for allegedly inflaming tensions between Hindus and Muslims, leading to clashes that left at least 40 dead and hundreds injured.
headline_main: Thousands of Bangladeshi Muslims Protest India Violence
headline_print_headline: Thousands of Bangladeshi Muslims Protest India Violence

abstract: Amy Klobuchar, Pete Buttigieg, Tom Steyer, Mike Bloomberg and perhaps Elizabeth Warren need to get out of the race.
snippet: Amy Klobuchar, Pete Buttigieg, Tom Steyer, Mike Bloomberg and perhaps Elizabeth Warren need to get out of the race.
lead_paragraph: It’s been a week of viruses and vitriol, jittery markets and even more jittery Democrats. Panic is in the air. Things are spinning out of control. The center cannot hold because there is no center in 2020.

abstract: The New Delhi force has been widely criticized for standing by during some of the worst religious violence in years. Its investigations, too, have prompted accusations of anti-Muslim bias.
snippet: The New Delhi force has been widely criticized for standing by during some of the worst religious violence in years. Its investigations, too, have prompted accusations of anti-Muslim bias.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI —  Indian police officers on Friday swooped down on neighborhoods in the capital that have been racked by religious violence this week, arresting more than a dozen people amid a brewing controversy over where to place blame for the bloodshed.

abstract: Investment-advisers are increasingly worried that U.S. authorities are not be doing enough to prevent a widespread outbreak of coronavirus in the country, potentially adding further downside to already-battered markets.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Investment-advisers are increasingly worried that U.S. authorities are not be doing enough to prevent a widespread outbreak of coronavirus in the country, potentially adding further downside to already-battered markets.
headline_main: Investment Advisers Worry U.S. Response to Coronavirus Is Too Little Too Late
headline_print_headline: Investment Advisers Worry U.S. Response to Coronavirus Is Too Little Too Late
